        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The Meritor Wabco System Saver 1200 with a pressure protection valve (PPV) does not allow enough
                    air volume to effectively purge the dryer desiccant cartridge during the purge cycle. (*Note that
                    suspect units are VIN specific. Not all units in the date range are involved.)
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury or death, shift transmission to park or neutral, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the supply (wet tank) and secondary air tanks until all the air has escaped from
                    all drain valves.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the air line and the pressure protection check valve from the air dryer (Figure
                    1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0691001" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0691001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Air Dryer</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Air Line</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Pressure Protection Check Valve</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove check valve parts from the valve (Figure 2) by removing the snap ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0691002" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/G0691002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Remove Check Valve Parts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Valve</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Check Valve</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Screen</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Snap Ring</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discard the check valve, screen and snap ring (Figure 2, Items 2, 3 and 4)</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply thread sealant to the valve external threads and re-install the valve to the air
                    dryer.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the air line to the valve and close the reservoir draincocks.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start the engine to charge the air system and check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
